        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 6:31PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of gusty winds
ahead of a strong thunderstorm extending from 10 miles northeast of
Bellview to 13 miles north of Saint Vrain, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clovis, Grady, Broadview, Wheatland, Bellview and Forrest.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
